cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for training deep neural networks with ternary weights and activations. It also addresses the issue of memory/computation consumption, which is a common concern in machine learning. Additionally, the paper mentions computer vision (cs.CV) as a potential application area for their proposed method. The paper also discusses the use of heuristic algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper's focus on hardware design and event-driven systems suggests that it could also belong to the categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
